<ul>
<li>
<p>I personally just encourage people to switch to KDE.</p>
<p>This "users are idiots, and are confused by functionality" mentality of Gnome is a disease. If you think your users are idiots, only idiots will use it. I don't use Gnome, because in striving to be simple, it has long since reached the point where it simply doesn't do what I need it to do.</p>
<p>Please, just tell people to use KDE.</p>
<ul>
<li>Torvalds, Linus (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2005-12-12">2005-12-12</span>). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mail.gnome.org/archives/usability/2005-December/msg00021.html">Message to usability@gnome.org mailing list</a>. Retrieved on 2006-08-28.</li>
