<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="2012">2012</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Linus_Torvalds&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: 2012">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul>
<li>We're not masturbating around with some research project. We never were. Even when Linux was young, the whole and only point was to make a *usable* system. It's why it's not some crazy drug-induced microkernel or other random crazy thing.
<ul>
<li>Torvalds, Linus (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2012-03-08">2012-03-08</span>). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://lkml.org/lkml/2012/3/8/495">Linus Torvalds -</a> <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_kernel_mailing_list" class="extiw" title="w:Linux kernel mailing list">LKML</a>. Retrieved on 2012-09-11.</li>
