<ul>
<li>Somebody is trying to kill all the kernel developers.</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>First we had two earthquakes - fine, this week God not only hates republicans, but apparently us kernel developers too. But we kernel developers laugh in the face of danger, and a 5.5 earthquake just makes us whimper and hide in the closet for a while.</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd>But after we've stopped cowering in the closet, there's a knock on the door, and the conference organizers are handing out skate boards, with the innocent explanations of "We're in San Diego, after all".</dd>
</dl>
<dl>
<dd>If that's not a sign of somebody trying to kill us, I don't know what is. Handing out skate boards to a bunch of geeks sounds like a seriously misguided thing to do.
<ul>
<li>Torvalds, Linus (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2012-08-26">2012-08-26</span>). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://plus.google.com/102150693225130002912/posts/K5sqXE3gB9o">Linus Torvalds - Google+</a>. Retrieved on 2012-08-27.</li>
</ul>
</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li>[…] I really hate big laptops. I can't understand people who lug around 15" (or 17"!) monsters. The right weight for a laptop is 1kg, no more.</li>
<li>Obsessing about things is important, and things really do matter, but if you can't let go of them, you'll end up crazy.</li>
